21/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu met with France's Supreme Court Chairman Guy Cavinet on Tuesday (20 January). They discussed the problems of organised crime and corruption and agreed that the judiciary plays a decisive role in the fight against them. They also discussed bilateral relations and opportunities for judicial co-operation. Moisiu said France's experience would be of major benefit to Albanian authorities, while Cavinet agreed on the need for joint programmes against crime. (ATA - 20/01/04)
